def is_stove_on(stove: item):
    # Function to check if the stove is on
    symbol stove_on=exists s: item : is_stove(s) and is_on(s)
    return stove_on

def is_pot_used_for_boiling(pot: item):
    # Function to check if the pot is being used for boiling
    symbol pot_used=has_water(pot)
    return pot_used

behavior cook_pasta(pasta:item, pot:item, stove:item):
    body:
        achieve inside(pasta, pot)
        # Place the pasta inside the pot

        achieve has_water(pot)
        # Add water to the pot

        achieve on(pot, stove)
        # Place the pot on the stove

        achieve is_on(stove)
        # Turn on the stove to cook the pasta

behavior cook_chicken(chicken:item, fryingpan:item, stove:item):
    body:
        achieve on(chicken, fryingpan)
        # Put the chicken in the frying pan

        achieve on(fryingpan, stove)
        # Place the frying pan on the stove

        achieve is_on(stove)
        # Turn on the stove to cook the chicken

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind stove: item where:
            is_stove(stove)

        bind pot: item where:
            is_pot(pot) and not is_pot_used_for_boiling(pot)
        # Select an unused pot for boiling

        bind fryingpan: item where:
            is_fryingpan(fryingpan)
        # Select a frying pan

        bind pasta: item where:
            is_dry_pasta(pasta)
        # Select the dry pasta

        bind chicken: item where:
            is_food_chicken(chicken)
        # Select the chicken

        cook_pasta(pasta, pot, stove)
        cook_chicken(chicken, fryingpan, stove)
